                  </hi>. I am the wife of Henry Atkins. I was going up Holborn on 5th May, between 8 and 9 o'clock in the evening—I had a purse and parcel in my hand—my purse was round my forefinger—the pri<lb></lb>soner snatched it from my hand and ran away—I had 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. in it—I saw the prisoner directly, and followed him—I did not lose sight of him—I was close behind him all the time—this is my purse (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>).</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did you see me take it? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, and followed you—I was in Holborn, nearly opposite Hatton-garden.</p>
